title: Congenital adrenal hyperplasia

title_lang.name: zh_title
title_lang.value: 先天性肾上腺皮质增生症

desc: An assortment of hereditary diseases that impact the adrenal glands—two walnut-sized organs located above the kidneys—are collectively referred to as congenital adrenal hyperplasia, or CAH. Important hormones that are produced by the adrenal glands include:One of the enzymes required to produce these hormones is absent in individuals with CAH due to a genetic mutation. Despite the fact that there is no known cure for congenital adrenal hyperplasia, most patients with the condition can recover with appropriate care. are able to live full lives.
